even considerate enough to inform Hope where the burial grounds of the tribe.<br>
<br>
The next day Hope and the merchant continued their trip. The band of theives attacked once more. The battle was almost won but for a thief who intended to use a knife on Hope. The merchant was very brave and noble, jumping forward to take the attack in Hope's place. As he fell to the ground wounded, Hope looked up and easily used her powers to defeat the remaining theives. A quick death for them was by no means painless.<br>
<br>
Hope looked to the merchant who had a fatal knife wound. She promised to ask the Nomain tribe to care for him, but he said it was unlikely. He had not heard from them for the past few months for reasons unknown. They were likely gone, at war or relocated for some reason. He knew his time was limited and that the Underworld would soon take him. He had but one dying request of Hope before he passed on.<br>
<br>
As Hope considered his brave sacrifice to save her, she wondered just what that one final request had been. She had left him lying there of course. She had a limited time to gain entry to the Nomain lands before Queen Asia or her right of caste noticed her. Still that bothered her to leave the man alone to die. Not the leaving him to die part. He was of no consequence. Just what was it that had been his last request. She sighed. Such considerations were always of mild annoyance to her and her far more important plans.<br>
<br>
She travelled onward... onward to the Nomain tribe and her third rune. And afterward, perhaps Smyrna.<br>
